supersonic — source package layout
==================================

This source package uses format 3.0 (quilt) with three upstream tarballs:

  supersonic_<v>.orig.tar.xz
      The upstream repository (git archive of the release tag), minus the
      Files-Excluded entries listed in debian/copyright.

  supersonic_<v>.orig-link.tar.xz
      Pristine Ableton Link 4.0 including its asio-standalone submodule
      (the GitHub tag tarball does NOT contain the submodule, so this is
      assembled from a recursive clone). Unpacks to link/. Upstream's four
      Link patches (kept in external/*.patch as the single source of truth)
      are applied to it via debian/patches/, path-shifted under link/.

  supersonic_<v>.orig-rust-vendor.tar.xz
      `cargo vendor` output for the committed rust/Cargo.lock. Unpacks to
      rust-vendor/; debian/rules points cargo at it and builds with
      --locked --offline.

All three tarballs, the path-shifted patches, and a snapshot changelog entry
are generated by upstream's scripts/make-debian-source.sh (run by upstream CI
in .github/workflows/debian.yml, which then builds the package in a
network-disconnected container, runs lintian and autopkgtest). A maintainer
can reuse that script or assemble the components by hand as described above.

Build dependencies deliberately come from the Debian archive: JUCE
(juce-modules-source + juce-tools), libsndfile, Boost headers, and Catch2
are the system packages, selected via the SUPERSONIC_SYSTEM_* CMake options.
See docs/DEBIAN-PACKAGING.md in the upstream tree for the full rationale and
the mapping table.
